seems like class$ might just be generated unused. I wonder if the dynamic report is still tracking its usage. Maybe there's an issue with invoking via Method.invoke being filtered? The coverage could be affected if JaCoCo isn’t marking synthetic methods. I'll need to look at other tests for similar behavior. If closure19 isn't compiled, it may remain uncovered. I should focus on a test that correctly exercises closure19.doCall instead of class$.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining class coverage issues**\\n\\nI want to inspect things further. The synthetic class$ is generated, but it seems there’s no caller for it. The dynamic reporter does ask for the Class.forName call in class$, but we didn't directly invoke it. This might be due to using \\\"io.restassured.internal.RequestSpecificationImpl\\\" in class$, which could already be loaded. I wonder if I should choose a class that's not already loaded. It seems like coverage doesn't care, since Class.forName is an API, but maybe the agent is filtering the results if the class name isn’t in the library.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pVxMQ6RiV0ZuGtiReixkSm3B|fc_04c839be205fba73016a2742127acc8193b04c1c28534f5409", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"dynamic-access|Class#forName|class\\$|coveredCalls|user-code-filter\" build.gradle forge tests/src -S | head -200", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4369, "output": 1528, "cacheRead": 40448, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46345, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780957677101, "responseId": "resp_04c839be205fba73016a2741ee161081939a73894ea6035368"}}
