ms like class$ might just be generated unused. I wonder if the dynamic report is still tracking its usage. Maybe there's an issue with invoking via Method.invoke being filtered? The coverage could be affected if JaCoCo isn’t marking synthetic methods. I'll need to look at other tests for similar behavior. If closure19 isn't compiled, it may remain uncovered. I should focus on a test that correctly exercises closure19.doCall instead of class$.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining class coverage issues**\\n\\nI want to inspect things further. The synthetic class$ is generated, but it seems there’s no caller for it. The dynamic reporter does ask for the Class.forName call in class$, but we didn't directly invoke it. This might be due to using \\\"io.restassured.internal.RequestSpecificationImpl\\\" in class$, which could already be loaded. I wonder if I should choose a class that's not already loaded. It seems like coverage doesn't care, since Class.forName is an API, but maybe the agent is filtering the results if the class name isn’t in the library.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pVxMQ6RiV0ZuGtiReixkSm3B|fc_04c839be205fba73016a2742127acc8193b04c1c28534f5409", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"dynamic-access|Class#forName|class\\$|coveredCalls|user-code-filter\" build.gradle forge tests/src -S | head -200", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4369, "output": 1528, "cacheRead": 40448, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46345, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780957677101, "responseId": "resp_04c839be205fba73016a2741ee161081939a73894ea6035368"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_pVxMQ6RiV0ZuGtiReixkSm3B|fc_04c839be205fba73016a2742127acc8193b04c1c28534f5409", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "build.gradle:601:        // Revert tests directory changes (including build.gradle and user-code-filter.json)\nforge/forge_metadata.py:45:from dataclasses import dataclass\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3024:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3040:    covered_calls = int(dynamic_access.get(\"coveredCalls\", 0) or 0)\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3054:    \"\"\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3060:        \"dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3061:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3066:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3196:        \"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3200:        \"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3219:        f\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3221:        \"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3223:        \"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4010:    \"\"\"Append issue context and concrete chunk limits for oversized dynamic-access runs.\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4015:    (§WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report).\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4049:            pipeline_argv.append(\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\")\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4834:    (§WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report).\nforge/forge_metadata.py:5090:    (§WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking, §GIT-issue-linking).\nforge/forge_metadata.py:6739:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:6742:    